article.description: — Bryce Hamilton had 26 points as UNLV defeated Nebraska Omaha 84-71 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Hamilton scores 26 to lift UNLV over Omaha 84-71
article.linkText: Hamilton scores 26 to lift UNLV over Omaha 84-71
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- — Bryce Hamilton had 26 points as UNLV defeated Nebraska Omaha 84-71 on Wednesday night. Royce Hamm Jr. had 16 points and 12 rebounds for UNLV (7-5). Donovan Williams added 12 points. Jordan McCabe had 11 points and Josh Baker 10. Felix Lemetti scored a career-high 20 points for the Mavericks (1-10), who have now lost 10 games in a row. Nick Ferrarini added 12 points. Darrius Hughes had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
